metadata.name: Syzers #97
metadata.description:
Syzers is a generative synthesizer project with sounds altered by Tone JS.

···· On Tuesday, May 17, unsold editions will be burned ····

Visually it consists of 16 layers, in which more than 350 elements are combined randomly, generating synthesizers with unique environments and landscapes.
As for the sound, 40 tracks were recorded with analog synthesizers that were then assigned to each of the modules. These, combined in groups of 4, provide thousands of possible combinations. 
In addition, these sounds will be further modified by code effects that will randomly vary their properties.

Click to listen to the sounds

Many thanks to @Jpupper and @Fipiaggio for help with programming the sound part and @Purespider for the template. 
"FXHASH PFP Token Generator" https://github.com/PureSpider/fxhash-pfp

for best resolution "open live" then use the "download image" button on the lower right corner ;)

metadata.name: Over the Air #231
metadata.description:
During the last couple of decades, over the air television signals and antennas switched to digital, bringing with them a new form of static and distortion as the signal is broken up. "Over the Air" is inspired by these digital distortions, incorporating aspects of them into the same grid-like structure seen on the television. Additional patterns are combined in the grid with these distortions to create the final artwork.

Patterns for the individual blocks in the grid are divided into categories, and various amounts are picked for each work, with dozens of possible mixtures. Patterns can flow in different directions across the varied canvases. Distribution of these patterns across the grid varies from work to work, providing for different feels as they bunch together or spread apart.

metadata.name: Farbteiler #455
metadata.description: Each Farbteiler is a rectilinear, mostly self-avoiding walk, dividing the space of the canvas with dotted grids using colors from Johannes Itten's Farbkreis. Everything is inside and everything is outside.

metadata.name: Elswhere #143
metadata.description:
Perlin noise walks into a Julia set and finds itself Elswhere. X is real, Y is imaginary, or is it the other way around? 

Elswhere is a unique generative art series in which noise and fractal math are combined to create whimsical shapes and motifs, with an infinite number of variations. Made with p5js.

For each pixel, the noise values corresponding to the X and Y coordinates are computed and then used as the real and imaginary components for initializing a Julia set recursion. The pixel is colored based on the number of steps it takes for the recursion to reach its base case.

Keyboard controls:
[S] Save the current view.
[2] Render 2000x3000px image.
[4] Render 4000x6000px image.
[6] Render 6000x9000px image.

Created by Elsif, 2022.05

metadata.name: Inertia #392
metadata.description:
This project will be reserved and free for 48 hours, for all the holders of any of my projects!

The amount of reserves for each user will be equal to the amount of all the token held at 13:00 CEST [UTC+2] (May 23)
(example: user holds 3 "Figment" and 2 "ACCUMULATOR", will be able to mint "Inertia" 5 times)

48h from now I will update the reserves list and burn the remaining tokens

WARINING: The reserves will expire 48h after the drop! And a price for the unlocked mintables will be set (unreserved mints will not be free).

---

"Inertia is a property of matter by which it continues in its existing state of rest or uniform motion in a straight line, unless that state is changed by an external force."

Particles are blasted from 2 to 4 sides of the canvas, each particle has its own mass and it has to traverse a friction-field, once it loses its momentum completely it stops and leaves a trace, adding or subtracting light from the canvas.

The friction-field has 18 possible mutation kinds.
Mutations are high-friction zones of various shapes.

Made just with JS on a canvas
right-click to save

metadata.name: Subdivisions #93
metadata.description:
As an artist with a background in engineering, I have always been a fan of technical drawings.
Architectural sketches and renderings fascinate me with their ability to visualize the conceptual.

I create generative art for the same reason - to reveal the beauty in an algorithm.

This project represents the division of space using techniques that, for me, call to mind sitting
at a drafting table, straight edge in hand, imagining what might be possible.

You can export a high resolution PNG (5000x5000) by pressing the 'e' key.

Twitter: @jeffpalmer
https://jpalmer.dev

metadata.name: Imaginary Resonances #265
metadata.description:
Some people describe creative coding as 'Computer Magick' and I agree, there is some degree of mysticism involved. Taking a physical phenomena and distorting it so that is no longer real is what Imaginary Resonances is about.

There is a surface and sand is dropped on it. The surface vibrates and ushers the sand into patterns. What kind of sound could have made the surface vibrate like that?

The algorithm behind Imaginary Resonances is simple variation on Chladni figures: figures that arise when sand is dropped on a vibrating surface.

Made by Sam Tsao (@sam___tsao) with p5

metadata.name: 7VV1N5 #439
metadata.description:
GO BIG OR GO HOME.

After a week of minimalism code, our hero, the handsome artist Daniel, decided he needed something involving maximalism to reset the balance. Finding pairs to put together is satisfying.

Images will take 6-9 seconds to display and refresh between window resizing.

Use the z key or single click/tap to switch to "zoom" mode, which zooms in and fills the viewport; use z & tap/click to cycle through views. Use x and double-click/tap to go back to square mode.

Note: It doesn't work on Internet Explorer, because Microsoft. iOS is faster than Android.

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

z, click, tap - Switch to & cycle "zoom" mode
x, double-click, double-tap - Switch back out of "zoom" mode.
h - Toggle high-res (slow)
s - Download and save image (takes a few seconds, longer for high-res)

metadata.name: The Space Inside #340
metadata.description:
Points fill in shapes on a warped noise field. The resulting images range from soft water colors to distorted, pixelated CRT screens. 

The image is drawn at 3000x3000px and scaled to the browser size. 

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 3000x3000px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume.

Features:
- Two palette sets
- Light or dark background
- 70% color image, 30% monochrome
- Various combinations of circles and rectangles
- All rectangles 
- 7 types of shapes: random circles, packed circles, checkerboard, orbs, ring, spiral, checkerboard and orbs
- Rectangles snap to a grid
- Fuzzy lines connected groups of drawing points
- Fuzzy lines around the dots
- Bright border on the shapes

Rare
- 9% to have a soft monochrome and color palette
